---
import PortalLayout from '../../layouts/PortalLayout.astro'
---

<PortalLayout
  title="Fellowship (Tier 4) — Sohma Institute"
  description="The Institute's highest credential. Two years of clinical leadership, original research, and protocol development across three or more divisions."
>
  <article class="tier-page">

    <!-- AT A GLANCE -->
    <header class="tier-header">
      <div class="section-label">Tier 4</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">Fellowship</h1>

      <div class="glance-strip">
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Duration</span>
          <span class="glance-val">2 years</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Mode</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Clinical Leadership + Research</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Credential</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Fellowship</span>
        </div>
        <div class="glance-divider"></div>
        <div class="glance-item">
          <span class="glance-key">Divisions</span>
          <span class="glance-val">Three or more simultaneously</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>


    <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Who this is for</h2>
      <p>Future Institute faculty, clinical leaders, and protocol developers. This is the Institute's highest credential and it's not a passive qualification — Fellows actively shape the institution. If you want to lead clinical teams, develop new protocols, supervise the next generation of practitioners, and contribute original research that changes how traditional medicine is practised, this is where that begins.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- WHAT FELLOWS DO -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>What Fellows do</h2>
      <p>This tier is as much about giving back to the Institute's ecosystem as it is about personal development.</p>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Original Research</h3>
          <p>Substantial research contribution that advances the Institute's knowledge base. Protocol validation studies, multi-site case series, methodological innovation. Published through the Institute's publishing arm.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Clinical Supervision</h3>
          <p>Supervise Tier 1–3 trainees. Mentor the next generation of practitioners. Your clinical experience becomes the training infrastructure for those who follow.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Protocol Development</h3>
          <p>Design, test, and refine clinical protocols. Move interventions through the research-to-bedside pipeline from investigational to validated. Shape how the network practises.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-card">
          <h3>Cross-Divisional Leadership</h3>
          <p>Operate across three or more divisions simultaneously. Lead complex case conferencing. Demonstrate the cross-divisional integration that the Institute's framework demands at its highest level.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- SELECTION -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Selection process</h2>
      <p>This reads more like a faculty appointment than a course enrolment. Selection is based on:</p>
      <div class="selection-list">
        <div class="selection-item">
          <span class="selection-num">1</span>
          <p><strong>Application & portfolio review</strong> — Your complete clinical portfolio from Tiers 1–3, including research output, case documentation, and supervisor evaluations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="selection-item">
          <span class="selection-num">2</span>
          <p><strong>Interview panel</strong> — Academic Board members and current Fellows assess clinical reasoning, research capability, and leadership potential.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="selection-item">
          <span class="selection-num">3</span>
          <p><strong>Demonstrated track record</strong> — Evidence of competency across multiple divisions. The cross-divisional requirement is non-negotiable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="selection-item">
          <span class="selection-num">4</span>
          <p><strong>Research proposal</strong> — A proposed research contribution that aligns with the Institute's current priorities and has clear clinical translation potential.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- OUTCOMES -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Outcomes</h2>
      <div class="pathway-cards">
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Fellow Network Membership</h3>
          <p>Protocol development privileges. Faculty appointment eligibility. Regional clinical governance leadership. The highest tier of the Practitioner Network.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 10v6M2 10l10-5 10 5-10 5z"/><path d="M6 12v5c3 3 8 3 12 0v-5"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Faculty Appointment</h3>
          <p>Eligibility for Institute faculty positions. Teaching, supervision, and curriculum development roles within your divisional specialisations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pathway-card">
          <div class="pathway-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="2" y1="12" x2="22" y2="12"/><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Clinical Governance</h3>
          <p>Regional clinical governance leadership. Shape how the Institute's protocols are implemented across the distributed practitioner network.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- FEES -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Fees & funding</h2>
      <p>The Fellowship operates on a different model to Tiers 1–3. Fellowship positions may include research funding, teaching stipends, or reduced tuition in exchange for supervisory and teaching commitments. The specifics depend on the Fellow's role within the Institute. Contact the Institute to discuss individual arrangements.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- PREREQUISITES -->
    <section class="tier-section">
      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <p>Graduate Diploma (Tier 3). Demonstrated competency across multiple divisions. Research output from Tier 3 that meets the Academic Board's standards for quality and clinical relevance.</p>
    </section>


    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="tier-cta">
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="#" class="cta-primary">Apply Now</a>
        <a href="#" class="cta-secondary">Enquire</a>
        <a href="/education" class="cta-secondary">Back to all programs</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</PortalLayout>

<style>
  .tier-page { font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif; color: var(--text-heading); padding: 0 clamp(24px, 4vw, 56px); }
  .tier-page p { line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .tier-page p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .tier-page h1, .tier-page h2, .tier-page h3 { margin: 0; }
  .section-label { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.25rem; font-size: 0.6875rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.18em; color: var(--accent-dark); margin-bottom: 1rem; white-space: nowrap; }
  .section-label::after { content: ''; flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--accent-line); }
  .tier-header { padding: 4rem 0 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-title { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-heading); line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 2rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .glance-strip { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .glance-item { padding: 0 1.5rem; } .glance-item:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
  .glance-key { display: block; font-size: 0.5625rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .glance-val { display: block; font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); }
  .glance-divider { width: 1px; height: 36px; background: var(--border-medium); flex-shrink: 0; }
  .tier-section { padding-bottom: 2.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-card); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .tier-section h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .tier-section p { font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-body-70); line-height: 1.8; }
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .content-card { background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .content-card h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .content-card p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }

  /* Selection process */
  .selection-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .selection-item { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; align-items: flex-start; }
  .selection-num {
    width: 32px; height: 32px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--accent-dark);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-border-20); flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .selection-item p { font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--text-body-70); line-height: 1.75; margin: 0; }
  .selection-item strong { color: var(--text-heading); }

  .pathway-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1rem; }
  .pathway-card { background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border-light); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .pathway-icon { color: var(--accent-dark); opacity: 0.6; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .pathway-card h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-heading); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .pathway-card p { font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-body-60); line-height: 1.7; }
  .tier-cta { padding: 2rem 0 4rem; }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .cta-primary { font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: #fff; background: var(--accent-dark); border-radius: 4px; padding: 12px 28px; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .cta-primary:hover { background: var(--accent-darker-hover); }
  .cta-secondary { font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--glass-12); border-radius: 4px; padding: 12px 28px; text-decoration: none; transition: border-color 0.2s, color 0.2s; }
  .cta-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent-border-30); color: var(--accent-dark); }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-title { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .glance-strip { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem; }
    .glance-divider { width: 60px; height: 1px; } .glance-item { padding: 0; }
    .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .pathway-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
